If we know for sure that the procList vector only holds a single element then rather than using a for loop use direct indexes like auto procTarget = procList[0] (it would be of less CPU cycles than of for loop). In case of multiple elements also we can write the for loop as for "(auto procTarget : procList)" no need to mention the data type explicitly although we can put a 'p' in front of procTarget to indicate it is a pointer, i.e.; pProcTarget
